<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Rao Leaves for Switzerland, Germany </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3101104994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0930 
GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3101104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister left <LOCATION>New Delhi</LOCATION> <TIME>this afternoon</TIME> on 
a six-day visit to <LOCATION>Switzerland</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Germany</LOCATION>. He was seen off at 
the airport by cabinet colleagues and senior officials. <PERSON>Mr. 
Narasimha Rao</PERSON> has been invited by the <ORGANIZATION>World Economic Forum</ORGANIZATION> to 
address the closing plenary of the symposium at <LOCATION>Davos</LOCATION> tomorrow. 
The prime minister is expected to apprise the world business 
community of the liberalization process in <LOCATION>India</LOCATION>. The theme for 
this year's <LOCATION>Davos</LOCATION> meet is redefining the basic assumptions of 
the world economy. The meeting of the forum, which began on 
<DATE>Tuesday</DATE>, is being attended by more than 20 heads of government 
and state. In all 800 company chief executives and 150 
government representatives are attending the deliberations. 
  From <LOCATION>Davos</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Mr. Rao</PERSON> will go on to <LOCATION>Bonn</LOCATION> on <DATE>Wednesday</DATE> on the 
second leg of his visit. He will hold talks with the German 
chancellor, <PERSON>Dr. Helmut Kohl</PERSON>. Both the leaders will address the 
Indo-German Business Conference. The prime minister will later 
go to <LOCATION>Berlin</LOCATION> where he will meet the German president. 

</TEXT>

