<H3> <TI>   Dalai Lama Cancels Visit to Frankfurt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1602172694 Hamburg DPA in German 1541 GMT 16 Feb 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1602172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Frankfurt/Main/Bonn (DPA) -- After warnings from 
<LOCATION>Bonn</LOCATION> because of the conflict between <LOCATION>China</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Tibet</LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION>Dalai 
Lama</ORGANIZATION>, the Tibetan leader, has declined an invitation to the 
1,200th anniversary of <ORGANIZATION>Frankfurt/Main</ORGANIZATION>. The <ORGANIZATION>Foreign Ministry</ORGANIZATION> had 
warned the city that the simultaneous invitation of the <ORGANIZATION>Dalai 
Lama</ORGANIZATION> and the mayor of <LOCATION>Frankfurt</LOCATION>'s Chinese partner city of 
<LOCATION>Guangzhou</LOCATION> could lead to "problems." On <DATE>Wednesday</DATE> [16 <DATE>February</DATE>] 
the <ORGANIZATION>Dalai Lama</ORGANIZATION>'s Swiss representative office declined the 
invitation that <LOCATION>Frankfurt</LOCATION> Mayor <PERSON>Andreas von Schoeler</PERSON> (Social 
Democratic Party of <LOCATION>Germany</LOCATION>) had extended to the <ORGANIZATION>Dalai Lama</ORGANIZATION>, who 
lives in exile in <LOCATION>India</LOCATION>. 
  The 58-year-old <ORGANIZATION>Nobel Peace Prize</ORGANIZATION> winner is calling for the 
reestablishment of the autonomous status of <LOCATION>Tibet</LOCATION>, which is 
under Chinese sovereignty. The statement of the Tibetan office 
in <LOCATION>Zurich</LOCATION> says the <ORGANIZATION>Dalai Lama</ORGANIZATION> had been very sorry to hear that 
his acceptance of the invitation had led to problems that had 
been created without his fault "as a result of obviously 
political motives." He wants to spare the city and its 
population difficulties. He had been pleased with the 
invitation, it was stated. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

