<H3> <TI>   Dalai Lama Warns Against `Strong Tolerance' Toward China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dalai Lama Warns Against `Strong Tolerance' Toward China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3004133994 Hamburg DPA in German 1012 GMT 30 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3004133994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Koenigswinter (DPA) -- The <LOCATION>Dalai Lama</LOCATION> has 
encouraged the <ORGANIZATION>FRG</ORGANIZATION> to take over responsibility in international 
politics. He hopes that, as a result of its special historical 
development, <LOCATION>Germany</LOCATION> will play an important role in establishing 
world peace, the secular and spiritual head of <LOCATION>Tibet</LOCATION> said in 
<LOCATION>Koenigswinter</LOCATION> near <LOCATION>Bonn</LOCATION> on <DATE>Saturday</DATE> [30 <DATE>April</DATE>]. 
  The <ORGANIZATION>Dalai Lama</ORGANIZATION>, who has lived in exile in <LOCATION>India</LOCATION> for 35 
years, 
pointed to the "particularly friendly relations" between <LOCATION>Germany</LOCATION> 
and <LOCATION>China</LOCATION>. However, this should not lead to a strong tolerance 
toward the <ORGANIZATION>Chinese Government</ORGANIZATION>. <LOCATION>Germany</LOCATION> has the opportunity to 
influence Chinese policy. The 58-year-old man stressed that 
awareness of the special situation in his homeland is widespread 
among the German public. 
  The Nobel Peace Prize laureate affirmed his path of 
nonviolence. "I am, on principle, against the use of weapons." 
This is also the basis of the support granted to the Tibetan 
people by the world public. The <ORGANIZATION>Dalai Lama</ORGANIZATION> is paying a 
three-day visit to <LOCATION>Germany</LOCATION> on the invitation of the 
<ORGANIZATION>Friedrich-Naumann Foundation</ORGANIZATION>, which is affiliated with the Free 
Democratic Party of <LOCATION>Germany</LOCATION>. 

</TEXT>

